gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Clippers 130, Warriors 125
gameRecap.excerpt: Despite Stephen Currys 41 points (9-19 3pt. FG), the Warriors fall to the Clippers, 130-125. James Harden recorded 26 points, eight rebounds and seven assists for the Clippers, while Paul George (24 points) and Norman Powell (21 points, 5-7 3pt. FG) added a combined 45 points in the victory. Brandin Podziemski tallied a career-high 25 points (5-5 3pt. FG), along with seven rebounds and eight assists for the Warriors in the losing effort. The Clippers improve to 36-17 on the season, while the Warriors snap a 5-game win streak and fall to 26-26.
